A simple shell script to pull the NASA astronomy picture of the day, save it,
and set it as the GNOME desktop background.

To install, link apod_wallpaper.sh somewhere in your $PATH, and add the crontab
entry in apod_schedule.

Tested with Ubuntu release 11.10 with GNOME 3.2.1

